Definition: causing injury or blight
Example: especially affecting with sudden violence or plague or ruin; the blasting effects of the intense cold on the budding fruit; the blasting force of the wind blowing sharp needles of sleet in our faces; a ruinous war
Synonyms: ruinous, causing, injury, or, blight, especially, affecting, with, sudden, violence, plague, ruin, the, effects, of, intense, cold, on, budding, fruit, force, wind, blowing, sharp, needles, sleet, in, our, faces, a, war
Category: adj.all
